            min_units: 3,
            max_units: 3,
            subject: "CHEM",
            catalog: "5810",
            req_group: 11187,
            description: "A basic study of the organic chemistry of natural and synthetic high polymers, their inherent properties and their uses in plastic, fiber, rubber, resin, food, paper and soap industries. Credit may not be given for both Chem 5810 and Chem 4810.  Prerequisite: Chem 1320. (Co-listed with MS&E 5810 and Chem Eng 5810)",
